Kevin Morgan, 55, was injured when a Land Rover Discovery reversed into his stationary Rover 75 in September 2005 .
He suffered whiplash, which developed into chronic pain syndrome and a deep depression .
The married engineer was filmed out walking, joking with a builder, in a coffee shop with his friend Max Clifford .
Mr Morgan claims he is in so much pain he only rarely leaves his house regularly .
Motor insurers Direct Line Group say Mr Morgan is exaggerating to an unconscionable degree .